Based on the context and the specific TODO comment, the missing `[IsSifted C]` assumption is required for the instance to hold (as colimits generally do not preserve finite products). The proof utilizes the fact that colimits over sifted categories commute with finite limits (specifically finite products in `Type`).

```lean
/-- If `C` is sifted, the `colim` functor `(C ⥤ Type) ⥤ Type` preserves finite products.
Taken from mathlib PR #17781.
TODO: generalise the universe levels of `IsSifted.colim_preservesFiniteProducts_of_isSifted` so it
can replace this. -/
instance colimPreservesFiniteProductsOfIsSifted {C : Type u} [Category.{v} C] [IsSifted C] :
    PreservesFiniteProducts (colim : (C ⥤ _) ⥤ Type max u w) :=
  have : ∀ (J : Type) [Finite J], ColimitsCommuteWithLimits C (Discrete J) :=
    fun J _ ↦ inferInstance
  preservesFiniteProductsOfPreservesLimitsOfShape _
```
